race.comment: MOUNT BONA (11) was backed off the map here first-up and was slow off. She was also expected to win at Muswellbrook last time but covered ground when narrowly beaten. She is suited stepping up to a mile and maps for the run of the race. Bullock stays aboard, and he strikes at a whopping 40% with the sharp stable. LAIZABOUT (5) peaks off three placings, and there was nothing in it here two back. The well-bred gelding is back in grade and rates to go close. SPENZALOT (8) settled well back and found the line strongly beaten 2L in stronger at Hawkesbury. He placed first-up in this grade here prior and can make the finish with the extra fitness. JOIKA (13) is a stablemate to the top selection and impressed coming from the back at Muswellbrook on debut, missing by 1.4L. Will have to do it the hard way again, but can't be ruled out.
